Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice half the @Apple{1} (all for 4 servings).

In a #small bowl{}, stir together @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} and @Cranberry Jam{1}.

  Lay @Sourdough Bread{4%slice} out on a clean work surface. Spread half the bread
slices with cranberry-Dijon jam. Layer with @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup} and as
many apple slices as you like. Top with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup} and
remaining bread slices.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium heat. Add sandwiches. Cook until bread is golden
brown and cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: You may need to work in batches, adding another drizzle of oil for each batch.

Cut grilled cheese sandos in half on a diagonal and divide between plates. Serve
with any remaining apple slices.